HTTPS Flow with CloudFront (SSL Termination)
User enters abc.com in browser → request is routed to Amazon CloudFront
CloudFront is associated with the domain abc.com, and the SSL certificate is issued via AWS Certificate Manager, which is trusted by Certificate Authorities.
Browser validates the certificate:
Checks if it is issued by a trusted CA
Verifies domain name (abc.com)
Once trusted, SSL/TLS handshake begins:
CloudFront sends its public key (from certificate)
Browser uses this public key to establish a secure session (generates session key)
Now communication becomes encrypted (HTTPS):
Browser sends encrypted request to CloudFront
At CloudFront:
SSL termination happens (HTTPS → HTTP)
Request is decrypted at edge location
CloudFront forwards the request to backend (e.g., Application Load Balancer)
